<span id="freeTextContainer3891500900682967851">One of Shaw&apos;s most unusual and enduringly popular plays. With SAINT JOAN (1923) Shaw reached the height of his fame and Joan is one of his finest creations; forceful, vital, and rebelling against the values that surround her. The play distils Shaw&apos;s views on the subjects of politics, religion and creative evolution.</span>
