<div id="review_3069664247" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3069664247" />
    <a title="Ananya M" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9613048-ananya-m"><img alt="Ananya M" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546859052p2/9613048.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3069664247?book_show_action=true">Dec 03, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ananya M" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ananya M" href="/user/show/9613048-ananya-m">Ananya M</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3069664247" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16905987741194988934">GB Shaw really has something in his words. This play was so good!! <br/>I always hear of Joan of Arc in passing but never read about her in detail. How much of this is true, I don’t know, but the fact that she was burnt at the stake for heresy and witchcraft in the 1400’s, only to be canonised in the 1900’s proves that she was doing the right thing. A poor 19 year old farm girl who believed in god and nothing else. She wanted to make France ‘free and French’. She wanted to defeat the English and give</span>
  <span id="freeText16905987741194988934" style="display:none">GB Shaw really has something in his words. This play was so good!! <br />I always hear of Joan of Arc in passing but never read about her in detail. How much of this is true, I don’t know, but the fact that she was burnt at the stake for heresy and witchcraft in the 1400’s, only to be canonised in the 1900’s proves that she was doing the right thing. A poor 19 year old farm girl who believed in god and nothing else. She wanted to make France ‘free and French’. She wanted to defeat the English and give France its rightful place back. She wanted to fight and serve her country. She appealed to everybody for help, and by the end of the play, everyone is a convert. They all see that she really is something and god really is on her side. And yet, she is burnt. <br />The story is really quite sad, but Shaw manages to inject some comic relief into it and all the characters are truly memorable. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16905987741194988934" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


